values.description: Allow ECS task to access S3 artifacts bucket
values.name: mlflow-dev-ecs-task

after.description: Allow ECS task to access S3 artifacts bucket
after.name: mlflow-dev-ecs-task

service_url.description: Service URL (custom domain if enabled, otherwise ALB DNS over HTTP).

description.constant_value: Allow ECS task to access S3 artifacts bucket

artifact_bucket_force_destroy.description: If true, allow Terraform to destroy the S3 bucket even if it contains objects (dev only).

container_image.description: Container image URI for the MLflow+Nginx image (e.g., <account>.dkr.ecr.<region>.amazonaws.com/mlflow:tag or public ECR).

container_port.description: Port exposed by the container (nginx listens on PORT env var).

db_name.description: Database name for MLflow backend store.

db_password.description: Database master password. If null, a random password is generated.

domain_name.description: Optional custom domain name for Route53/ACM (e.g., mlflow.example.com). Leave null to use ALB DNS name and HTTP only.

enable_https.description: If true, create ACM cert + HTTPS listener. Requires domain_name and hosted_zone_id.

hosted_zone_id.description: Route53 hosted zone ID for domain_name. Required if domain_name is set.

mlflow_password.description: Comma-delimited passwords for basic auth (passed to container).

mlflow_username.description: Comma-delimited usernames for basic auth (passed to container).
